{{distinguish|Créolité}}
'''Créolie''' is a literary movement in the island of [[Réunion]], a French [[overseas department]] in the [[Indian Ocean]] east of [[Madagascar]]. The term was coined by [[Jean Albany]] (1917–1984) and was developed in his poetry and painting. It attracted figures like [[Gilbert Aubry]], a Réunion poet and bishop.<ref>Noirs, Cafres et Créoles. Études de la représentation du non-Blanc réunionnais. Documents et littératures réunionnaises (1710-1980), Rose May-Nicole, Éditions L'Harmattan, Paris, 1996 – {{ISBN|2-7384-4615-9}}.</ref>

