{{Infobox record label <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Music --> | name = EPM Musique | founded = {{start date|1986}} | founder = François Dacla | genre = [[Chanson]], theater, spoken word, jazz | country = France | location = <!-- headquarters city and state --> | url = {{URL|www.epmmusique.fr}} }}
'''EPM Musique''' is a French record label that was created in 1986 by François Dacla,<ref>Jacques Vassal. ''[https://books.google.fr/books?id=RYqkipx7-dUC&pg=PP190 Léo Ferré, la voix sans maître]''. Le Cherche Midi. 2003. P. 190. Accessed on line 18 December 2015.</ref> former president of [[RCA]] France.<ref>[https://books.google.fr/books?id=DCUEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PT92 "French Labels Lags Behind In Video Market"]. ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''. Vol. 92, No 40. 4 October 1980. P. 77.</ref> The label specializes in [[Chanson]] and its legacy. It is also dedicated to poetry, theatre, and children's music.
"EPM is a French label whose interests include classic American jazz from the '30s through '50s."<ref>''CD Review''. Vol. 6, Nos 1-6. 1989. Page xlviii.</ref> The label reissued earlier [[jazz]] recordings.<ref>David Dicaire. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=ug9FPHAvcbcC Jazz Musicians of the Early Years, to 1945]''. McFarland. 2003. P.16, 19,28, 56, 79. Accessed on line 18 December 2015.</ref><ref>Frank Hoffmann. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=-FOSAgAAQBAJ Encyclopedia of Recorded Sound]''. Routledge. 2004. P.152, 1071. Accessed on line 18 December 2015.</ref><ref>"For now, the best one-CD collection is ''Jazz Gitan 1939-1943'' (EPM Musique)". Michael Dregni. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=jG3nBwAAQBAJ Gypsy Jazz: In Search of Django Reinhardt and the Soul of Gypsy Swing]''. Oxford University Press. 2008. Accessed on line 18 December 2015.</ref> [[Memphis Minnie]]'s recordings were particularly reissued.<ref>Paul and Beth Garon. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=IerXAwAAQBAJ Woman with Guitar: Memphis Minnie's Blues]''. City Lights Books. 2014. P.328-49. Accessed on line 18 December 2015.</ref>
Most of its catalog is distributed by [[Universal Music Group]].
==Artists== * [[Léo Ferré]]<ref>Robert Wangermée. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=70wwbh-ZXYkC Dictionnaire de la chanson en Wallonie et à Bruxelles]''. Editions Mardaga. 1995. P.231.</ref> * [[Anne Sylvestre]] * [[Michèle Bernard]] * [[Georges Chelon]] * [[Marc Ogeret]] * [[Marc Robine]] * [[Francis Lemarque]] * [[Monique Morelli]] * [[Hélène Martin]] * [[Julos Beaucarne]] * [[Diane Dufresne]] * [[Anna Prucnal]] * [[Anne Vanderlove]] * [[Claudine Lebègue]] * [[Francesca Solleville]] * [[Marcel Dadi]] * [[Pierre Dac]] * [[Michel Buhler]] * [[Jean Vasca]] * [[Pierre Meige]]
