{{Harvcoltxt|Thompson|1965}} says that in Hanoi, words spelled with ''ưu'' and ''ươu'' are pronounced {{IPA|/iw, iəw/}}, respectively, whereas other dialects in the Tonkin delta pronounce them as {{IPA|/ɨw/}} and {{IPA|/ɨəw/}}. This observation is also made by {{Harvcoltxt|Phạm|2008}} and {{Harvcoltxt|Kirby|2011}}.

==Final stops==
When stops {{IPA|/p, t, k/}} occur at the end of words, they have [[no audible release]] ({{IPA|[p̚, t̚, k̚]}}):

:{| cellpadding="5" style="line-height: 1.0em;"
| ''đáp''
| 'to reply'
| {{IPA|/ɗap/}}
| →
| {{IPA|[ɗap̚]}}
|-
| ''mát''
| 'cool'
| {{IPA|/mat/}}
| →
| {{IPA|[mat̚]}}
|-
| ''khác''
| 'different'
| {{IPA|/xak/}}
| →
| {{IPA|[xak̚]}}
|}

When the velar consonants {{IPA|/k, ŋ/}} are after {{IPA|/u, o, ɔ/}}, they are articulated with a simultaneous bilabial closure {{IPA|[k͡p̚, ŋ͡m]}} (i.e. [[doubly articulated]]) or are strongly [[labialization|labialized]] {{IPA|[k̚ʷ, ŋʷ]}}.

